###How to fix the Web Threats issue of 
The Web Threats issue in Apache web server can be fixed by disabling the TRACE HTTP method in Apache Configuration. You can do this by modifying/adding the following directive in your httpd.conf of your Apache Web Server:

```
TRACE disabled
```

This will prevent attackers from using the TRACE method to exploit vulnerabilities in your web server.

The Web Threats issue belongs to the OWASP Top 10 Web 2021 category of Injection. Injection attacks are a type of attack where an attacker injects malicious code into a vulnerable application. This malicious code can then be executed by the application, allowing the attacker to gain control of the application or steal data.

Here are some other steps you can take to secure your Apache web server:

* Keep your Apache web server up to date with the latest security patches.
* Use a strong password for your Apache web server account.
* Configure your Apache web server to only listen on the ports that you need.
* Use a firewall to block traffic to your Apache web server from unauthorized sources.
* Use a web application firewall (WAF) to protect your Apache web server from common web application attacks.

By taking these steps, you can help to protect your Apache web server from attack.
